ce:section.ce:para:
In the present study, the sol–gel method was employed to form a molecular imprinting layer by co-polymerization on the N-CDs, with TOB and N-CDs as template molecules and fluorescent sources, APTES and TEOS as aggregate elements. After elution and extraction of the template molecules, the molecular fluorescent probe of N-CDs@MIPs as obtained (
                     Scheme 1

                     ). Among the investigations that have appeared so far, this work is the first report in the field of TOB determination using a molecular fluorescent probe prepared by molecular blotting coupling on the surface of quantum dots. The present study differs from the recognition mechanism and luminescence phenomenon of other sol–gel prepared CDs@MIPs in that the probe shows a significant fluorescence enhancement when it is coupled to TOB. The N-CDs@MIPs probe both improves the specificity of N-CDs and gives MIPs a better signal output capability, solving the drawbacks when both are present alone. The developed fluorescent probe met the process requirements for TOB trace detection in actual milk samples with high precision and accuracy.
